# JavaScript Conventions

## No Frameworks or Build Tools

This project uses **vanilla JavaScript only**. Do not introduce React, Vue, jQuery, or any npm dependencies.

## Entry Point Pattern

All code lives inside a single `DOMContentLoaded` listener in `script.js`:

```js
// ✅ GOOD — wrap everything in DOMContentLoaded
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    // feature 1
    // feature 2
});

// ❌ BAD — do not add inline <script> logic in index.html (except lucide.createIcons())
```

## DOM Selection

```js
// ✅ Prefer getElementById for unique elements
const navbar = document.getElementById('navbar');

// ✅ Use querySelectorAll for groups
document.querySelectorAll('.os-text').forEach(el => { ... });

// ❌ Avoid unnecessary repeated queries — store references in variables
```

## Event Handling

- Attach listeners via `addEventListener`, never via `onclick=""` HTML attributes
- Use arrow functions for inline callbacks; use named functions for reusable logic

## Async / Timers

- Use `setTimeout` / `setInterval` for animations and deferred work
- Prefer `const` and `let`; never use `var`

## Lucide Icons

After dynamically adding new elements with `data-lucide` attributes, call `lucide.createIcons()` again to render them:

```js
container.innerHTML = '<i data-lucide="star"></i>';
lucide.createIcons(); // re-run to pick up new icons
```
